title: For Sale/Trade:  One of a kind knife for that one of a kind individual
location: Dadeville - Bham - Huntsville, Alabama, United States
postcontent:
I made this knife from locally sourced parts and did everything by hand. I began with a ferrier's file and annealed the steal in a wood fire. I then shaped and shaved the steel with a file and sanding to get the desired profile. Once initial profile was complete I tempered the steel again in a wood fire and quenched in a mixture of used motor oil and transmission fluid giving it a soft but super sharp edge perfect for skinning your price in the field. The handle was made from a sail boat on the lake that no longer enjoys the spray and wind and were pressed together using fiberglass resin to make the micarta. (a messy nasty process I can tell you) Once the handle was installed and shaped with scallops for a superior grip I shaped the final bevel to have two different angles. The purpose behind this was to make a knife similar to those the native americans and inuits used processing their game. The bevel allows the blade to slice along the top of the muscle much easier than with conventional angled bevels. 

Sharpening the blade is as easy as a few runs on a sharpening rod and you are back to shaving your game in no time. 

i have over 30 hours in this project and would like to pass it on to someone else you appreciates a knife no one else on the planet has like it. Will also include a kydex sheath custom made for this blade that enables right or left hand carry as well as a modified scout carry. If you are looking for a quality blade that jim, jack, harry, and dumbass doesn't have then this is the blade for you. 

Sale Price $250
Trade Value $300

title: For Sale:  NEW IN BOX NEVER FIRED Windham Weaponry SRC AR Rifle 223/556
location: N. Raleigh, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
Windham Weaponry SRC
Model# R16M4FTT
Made in the U.S.A.
BRAND NEW – NEVER FIRED

The Windham Weaponry SRC is a sight-ready, semi-automatic carbine chambered in .223 Rem. or 5.56 NATO. Long story short, Windham Weaponry used to be Bushmaster Arms. The owner of Bushmaster sold the company to Remington and then in early 2011, he bought it back and renamed it Windham Weaponry. Windham currently has three AR-15 carbines in their catalog. What makes the SRC unique compared to the other two (MPC and HBC) is that instead of sights it has a Picatinny rail for easy mounting of a scope or optics and it costs about $50 less.  The SRC uses a gas impingement operating system, meaning the propellant gases that push the projectile out of the bore are captured in a tube near the muzzle. The tube directs the gas backwards toward the bolt and ultimately push the bolt back and cycling the action.  Features include 6 position telescoping buttstock, which allows shooters to adjust the stock to his or her liking, and the receiver is made of 7075 T6 aircraft aluminum, which is a corrosion resistant alloy. The material was originally designed by the Japanese in the 1940s for fighter jet frames. Now it’s commonly used to make bikes, planes, boats, cars and firearms.  Also includes black web sling and hard plastic carrying case.

Specifications:
Caliber: .223 Rem.or 5.56 NATO
Capacity: 30 + 1
Sights:	 None
Features: Gas piston operating system
Action: Semi-auto
Stock: 6 Position telescoping buttstock
Material/Finish: Forged 7075 T6 aircraft aluminum/hardcoat black anodize 
Barrel: 16” M4 profile, chrome lined with A2 flash suppressor, made of 4150 chrome moly vanadium 11595E steel
Scope: Picatinny rail
Weight: 6.2 pounds
Barrel length: 16"
Twist: 1 in 9"
Overall length: 30 to 34.5"
MSRP: $1,040

Buyer pays additional $25 FFL transfer fee to be paid to Carolina Gunrunners at 1141 Falls River Avenue, Raleigh, NC at time of sale.
